args:
The rain Yggdrasil calls to nourish the forest is
a natural disaster to its neighbors. When Luca
breaks his oath and reveals the existence of the
secret remedy to save their lives, the townsfolk
take to the forest with axes in hand.
(I can't stop thinking about the noise\nI heard when I was out with Isaac.)
Keep making that face and it'll stick that\nway. What's on your mind, Sis?
Oh, er... Let me start by filling you in on\nwhat happened yesterday.
A loud rumbling from the town? We\ndidn't hear anything here in the village.
Well, I definitely heard it at the forest's\nedge! It keeps playing over and over in\nmy head.
That's what's got you looking so tense?\nSounds like an easy fix to me. Let's go!
Y'know, sometimes I really am proud to\nhave such a go-getter of a big brother!
Glad to meet your exacting standards.\nNow, c'mon. Let's check it out!
The town... It's in ruins!\nWhat's happening?!
Are you okay? I'm seeing a lot of injured\nfolks. What's the story here?
The god of the forest is bringing disaster\nupon us all! This town's finished, it is!
Whoa, slow down there, buddy.\nI'm sure that's not—
No. What he's saying is true.
You're sylvan, aren't you?\nBut you live here in this town?
Yeah. I was born in the forest, but the old\nInitio ways and I weren't a great match.
So I left it behind and built a new town out\nhere. That was two hundred years ago.
YOU built this whole town?!\nThat's amazing!
You can still see the old forest here,\nbut we live unshackled from its laws.
That appealed to some sylvans. Humans\nand others, too. They gathered here, and\nan outpost became a village, then a town.
It was a nice place to live...\n'Til things started going haywire recently.
The forest's spreading. Lately, it's even\nstarted creeping into town.
It's Yggdrasil. Not that it's doing it out of\nany malice towards us. It just lives its life.
Yggdrasil is the guardian of the forest.\nIt protects and fosters all life equally.

But that's not how things work in a town.
We grow the crops that we need, and
weed out the rest. We kill harmful animals
and pests.
We couldn't go on living if we didn't.
Same goes for the rains. I'm sure Yggdrasil\nis just providing the forest with what it\nneeds to grow.
But the effects of storms like that on\nopen land we've cleared of trees can be\ncatastrophic...like yesterday's landslide.
Ah! So that WAS what I heard from the\nforest outskirts yesterday.
Each new disaster creates more sick and\ninjured, and fewer resources to help them.
Even if we decided to give up on this place\nand relocate, a lot of us here physically\ncan't move.
So they just lie and wait for the end to\ncome. I'm afraid this town is finished.
I'm with Sarisse. Even if the town can't be\nsaved, you can't give up on people's lives!
I'm not exactly keen on the idea,\nbut it's not like I have a choice!
I can't just sit by and let them die.\nThese people have done nothing wrong!
Remedy? What are you talking about?
In Initio, they've got this miracle cure\nthey make from leaves steeped in\nYggdrasil's mana.
A single dose, and even a serious injury'll\nheal up in the blink of an eye!
But it's forbidden to tell anyone outside of\nthe forest about it, so let me go ask for a\nfew doses for the people here.
Sit tight until I come back.
(I can't believe he would just violate one\nof the laws they've held to for so long...)
(I understand these people's plight, and I\ncan relate to wanting to help them, but\nstill!)
(At the very least, I have to go tell Isaac\nbefore anything happens.)
Isaac! Thank goodness you're finally back.
Sarisse? What has you so shaken?
There's something you need to hear about.\nEarlier today, we were—
Huh? Isaac, wait! Where are you going?!
No, stop! Please, just wait!\nI told you I'd go and talk to them!
We're in no condition to just sit and wait!\nYou saw the state of our town. You should\nknow how urgent this is!
Stop this! What are you people doing?!
Explain this, Luca. Who are these people?\nWhy have they entered the forest without\npermission?
We're sylvans from the town just outside\nthese woods.
We've come for the spiritree.\nWe need this remedy of yours!
I'm...I'm sorry. I didn't think they'd\ncome try to take the stuff by force!
Listen, folks, I'm begging you to calm\ndown. It doesn't have to be like this.\nWe can all come to an agreement here!
We don't have time to negotiate!\nIf we don't act now, people will die!
The laws of Initio are the teachings of our\nancestors. They won't give them up, even if\nit means lives are lost!
That strict adherence to tradition is why\nthis place remains a holy land to our kind.\nI take pride in that, as a fellow sylvan.
But traditions won't save our friends and\nfamilies from the swift advance of an\nimminent and painful death!
Do you have any idea what will happen if\nyou chop down that tree?!
This forest is Yggdrasil's life itself.\nAnd among all that grows here, that\nspiritree is Yggdrasil's flesh and bone.
Its boughs are replete with Yggdrasil's\nmana. To take an axe to them is to cut\ndown Yggdrasil itself!
And what of it?! Yggdrasil's been making a\nharvest of our lives for years now!
NO! Leave the tree be, I say!
I'm a sylvan, same as you. I know just how\nimportant Yggdrasil and this forest are.
But is it a crime to try to protect OUR way\nof life?! Sorry, but we're taking this branch\nwith us!
WAIT! As a guardsman of the verdure,\nI cannot allow—
Yggdrasil is suffering... Rgh.\nAt this rate, its very life is in danger!
Isaac! C'mon, Luca.\nWe've got to go after him!
